<br>
I was charming manticores (yes those amazing undercons that hit like a Mack truck), casting swift like the wind on them, then pulling frost giant savages to them with tash and letting them go to town.<br>
<br>
It was... frankly... amazing.  I was getting about 4 giants to the pet with zero downtime and no real effort on the part of either me or my druid partner.<br>
<br>
Then I got cocky and pulled 2 giants, root parking 1 of them nearby while waiting for my pet to finish the first.  Druid's snare on the giants got resisted a couple times.  Sow wore off.  Snare on the pet wore off.  Root on giant 2 wore off.  Charm wore off.  The giant never had a chance to get at either of us... yes the manticore killed us both THAT quick. Lol.  Still I think I came out ahead on experience from how well we had done earlier with this method.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
If you like living on the edge... go for it.  But try not to get your entire group wiped out in a bad spot.<br>
